\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces REnFormer architecture. A shared encoder processes each site's lookback window independently. Each raw-MW window is renormalised by its own statistics, projected and position-encoded, passed through $L$ post-LayerNorm Transformer blocks, and re-combined with the projected input via a macro skip connection (dashed). The last token is pooled and projected to Gaussian parameters for the forecast horizon, then de-normalised back to MW. Total: 536\,k parameters.}}{4}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{1}{4}{REnFormer architecture. A shared encoder processes each site's lookback window independently. Each raw-MW window is renormalised by its own statistics, projected and position-encoded, passed through $L$ post-LayerNorm Transformer blocks, and re-combined with the projected input via a macro skip connection (dashed). The last token is pooled and projected to Gaussian parameters for the forecast horizon, then de-normalised back to MW. Total: 536\,k parameters}{figure.1}{}}
